120
0:05:06.26,000 --> 0:05:08,000
of coercion, "sticks,"

121
0:05:08.26,000 --> 0:05:1,000
you can do it with payments,

122
0:05:10.26,000 --> 0:05:12,000
"carrots,"

123
0:05:12.26,000 --> 0:05:14,000
or you can do it by getting others

124
0:05:14.26,000 --> 0:05:16,000
to want what you want.

125
0:05:16.26,000 --> 0:05:19,000
And that ability to get others to want what you want,

126
0:05:19.26,000 --> 0:05:21,000
to get the outcomes you want

127
0:05:21.26,000 --> 0:05:23,000
without coercion or payment,

128
0:05:23.26,000 --> 0:05:26,000
is what I call soft power.

129
0:05:26.26,000 --> 0:05:29,000
And that soft power has been much neglected

130
0:05:29.26,000 --> 0:05:31,000
and much misunderstood,

131
0:05:31.26,000 --> 0:05:34,000
and yet it's tremendously important.

132
0:05:34.26,000 --> 0:05:37,000
Indeed, if you can learn

133
0:05:37.26,000 --> 0:05:39,000
to use more soft power,

134
0:05:39.26,000 --> 0:05:41,000
you can save a lot

135
0:05:41.26,000 --> 0:05:43,000
on carrots and sticks.

136
0:05:43.26,000 --> 0:05:46,000
Traditionally, the way people thought about power

137
0:05:46.26,000 --> 0:05:49,000
